To see when we get complex eigenvalues for the system, we plug

\begin{align*}
\tau^{2} - 4 \cdot \Delta < 0
\implies (1 - 3 x_{0}^{2})\cdot\frac{1}{\sigma} - \frac{4a}{\sigma} < 0
\end{align*}

Now substituting for $x_{0} = -\frac{b}{a}$ we get $\implies 0 < a^{2} - 4a^{3} < 3b^{2}$ and $a < \frac{1}{4}$. Hence, we get $|b| = \sqrt{\frac{a^{2}-4a^{3}}{3}}$\\  


